@startmindmap
* Linux Isolation\n(Defense in Depth)
** Threat model shift
*** Castle model insufficient
*** Compromise assumed
*** Least privilege internally
** Filesystem
*** mount options\n(nosuid, noexec, nodev, ro)
*** chroot\n(not a security boundary)
** Network
*** netfilter\n(iptables, nftables, ufw, bpfilter)
** Resources
*** cgroups\n(cpu, memory, pids, devices)
** Kernel partitioning
*** namespaces\n(mnt, pid, net, ipc, uts, user, cgroup, time)
*** Plan 9 heritage
*** clone / unshare / setns
** Virtualization
*** Containers\n(shared kernel)
*** Type-2 hypervisor\n(hosted)
*** Type-1 hypervisor\n(bare metal)
*** Qubes OS\n(security by compartmentalization)
** Composition cost
*** Primitives combine like legos
*** Exponential complexity
*** Security by obscurity risk
@endmindmap
